org.transitime.gtfs.gtfsStructs

Class GtfsStop

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.transitime.utils.csv.CsvBase
      • org.transitime.gtfs.gtfsStructs.GtfsStop

  • public class GtfsStop
extends CsvBase
    A GTFS stops object. Contains two extension columns beyond the GTFS spec, hidden and adherenc.stop. They are useful for the user interface. They will usually be set using a supplemental stops file.
    Author:
    SkiBu Smith

      • getTimepointStop

        public java.lang.Boolean getTimepointStop()
        Specifies if system should determine schedule adherence times for this stop. Some agencies configure all stops to have times but determining schedule adherence for every single stop would clutter things up. Only want to show adherence for a subset of stops.
        Returns:
        null if not set in config files

      • shouldDeleteFromRoute

        public boolean shouldDeleteFromRoute(java.lang.String routeShortNameToDeleteFrom,
                                     java.lang.String routesStr)
        Returns true if the routeShortNameToDeleteFrom specified is defined in deleteFromRoutes.
        Parameters:
        routeShortNameToDeleteFrom - The short name of the route currently working on. Used to determine if the stop really should be deleted.
